fullplot: In the Indonesian Forrest lives a Danish loner, Severin Geertsen (Nikolaj Coster-Waldau). He kills some english journalist, because they get close to a speciel white flower. The danish psyckologist Adrian (Nikolaj Lie Kaas) and his assistent, Beate (Birgitte Hjort Sèrensen), travels to Indonesia to do a mental check on Severin, who claims that he is 129 years old because the flowers leaves kept him young. Adrian, Severin and Beate ends up being hunted in the name of getting the flower that gives eternal live.
